                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/4229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 3, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. Your 134, June 27, 9 p.m. The Department has had no indication that the
                    American Republics intend to make collective representations urging Spain to
                    remain out of the war. This idea was broached to the Under Secretary by the
                    British Ambassador, however, in approximately the manner it was mentioned to
                    you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
